{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d5776f5c-d239-488e-a3d2-d09d7631b8bf","content":"`adjustResize` was deprecated by Android in API 30 and is no longer reliable. The modern replacement uses **Android's `WindowInsets` API** to detect the keyboard (IME) and adjust padding. Here's how to do it in .NET 10 MAUI:\n\n### 1. Layout your chat page with a `Grid`\n\n```xml\n<!-- ChatPage.xaml -->\n<ContentPage x:Class=\"MyApp.ChatPage\">\n  <Grid RowDefinitions=\"*, Auto\">\n    <CollectionView Grid.Row=\"0\" ItemsSource=\"{Binding Messages}\"\n                    ItemTemplate=\"{StaticResource MessageTemplate}\" />\n    <Grid Grid.Row=\"1\" ColumnDefinitions=\"*, Auto\" Padding=\"8\">\n      <Entry Placeholder=\"Type a message...\" />\n      <Button Grid.Column=\"1\" Text=\"Send\" />\n    </Grid>\n  </Grid>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n### 2. Handle keyboard insets on Android\n\nIn **`Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`**:\n\n```csharp\nusing Android.Views;\nusing AndroidX.Core.View;\n\npublic class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity\n{\n    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)\n    {\n        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);\n\n        // Opt into edge-to-edge so insets are delivered instead of\n        // relying on the deprecated adjustResize mode.\n        WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window!, false);\n\n        var content = Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;\n        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(content, new KeyboardInsetsListener());\n    }\n\n    private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener\n    {\n        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)\n        {\n            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());\n            var navBar   = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());\n\n            // Use whichever is taller: the keyboard or the nav bar\n            int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navBar.Bottom);\n            view.SetPadding(view.PaddingLeft, view.PaddingTop, view.PaddingRight, bottom);\n\n            return insets;\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 3. (Optional) Disable MAUI's auto-scroll for that page\n\n`KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (on by default) tries to scroll to the focused entry, which can conflict. Disable it on your chat page:\n\n```csharp\n// ChatPage.xaml.cs\n#if ANDROID\nusing Microsoft.Maui.Platform;\n#endif\n\nprotected override void OnAppearing()\n{\n    base.OnAppearing();\n#if ANDROID\n    KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Disconnect();\n#endif\n}\n\nprotected override void OnDisappearing()\n{\n    base.OnDisappearing();\n#if ANDROID\n    KeyboardAutoManagerScroll.Connect();\n#endif\n}\n```\n\n### How it works\n\n| Old (deprecated) | New (API 30+) |\n|---|---|\n| `adjustResize` shrinks the window | `WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(…, false)` opts into edge-to-edge |\n| OS handled layout shift | You apply bottom padding from `WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime()` |\n\nThe insets listener fires whenever the keyboard opens/closes, adjusting the bottom padding of your root content view so the input bar slides up above the keyboard. This is the approach Android itself recommends as the replacement for `adjustResize`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9ce8a82a-069b-4e39-bc5d-47409132ec0d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI issue where the keyboard covers the bottom text input on Android. They mention that `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` no longer works in .NET 10. This is a known change — Android itself deprecated `adjustResize` in API 30+, and .NET MAUI has been evolving its approach.\n\nLet me think about what I know:\n\nIn .NET MAUI / Android, the `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was the go-to approach, but Android deprecated `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` in API 30 (Android 11). \n\nThe modern approach involves using `WindowInsets` and edge-to-edge display instead. In .NET 8+, MAUI introduced `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` which automatically handles keyboard scrolling, though for more control I might need to use platform-specific Android code with `WindowInsetsCompat` API. Building the chat layout...\n\nActually, I'm reconsidering the approach here. The user mentioned that `AdjustResize` doesn't work anymore in newer Android versions, so I need to shift to the modern `WindowInsets` API instead. The key is disabling the default system window fitting and then manually handling the keyboard insets to adjust the layout padding when the IME appears.\n\nSetting up the Android handler... Setting up keyboard insets...\n\nActually, let me reconsider what actually works in MAUI. The most straightforward approach is setting the soft input mode in the Android activity, though that's deprecated and apparently not working for this user. The modern way involves edge-to-edge rendering with proper insets handling, or I could explore MAUI's built-in keyboard handling options.\n\nFor .NET 10 specifically, I should focus on the insets-based approach since that's the current Android standard, combined with disabling any auto-scroll behavior that might interfere with the layout adjustments.","outputTokens":2708,"requestId":"0460:28DFFE:13633F6:15BDE67:6A027C68"},"id":"e27a3173-6262-4228-a489-e348f147350a","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:04:27.154Z","parentId":"076420f8-0449-4ea4-86cb-c17e39ceadbb"}
